  <span id="freeText1898268247940287353" style="display:none">Yes, Ms. Kingsolver knows her way around a pretty turn of phrase. <br /><br /> In this book, however, she uses her pretty language to dress up an unlikeable bitch and then she harangues us - on and on - about global warming, the sins of buying shoddy goods made overseas, the shameful state of rural education, hmmm, did I miss anything? People make SPEECHES in this book, as if it were conversation. <br /><br /> And then she has the less-bitchy friend of the bitch woman throw in old chestnuts from church bulletin boards, which, trust me, you've read before, and they weren't that funny the first time.<br /><br /> Dude. Those of us who read your books are the choir. Quit preaching at US.</span>
