<div id="review_1022305261" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1022305261" />
    <a title="Phrynne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8655084-phrynne"><img alt="Phrynne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640891977p2/8655084.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1022305261?book_show_action=true">Aug 09, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Phrynne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Phrynne" href="/user/show/8655084-phrynne">Phrynne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1022305261" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4289695674154612529">Well that was my first <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3541.Barbara_Kingsolver' title='Barbara Kingsolver' rel='nofollow noopener'>Barbara Kingsolver</a> book and since everyone seems to agree it is not her best then I certainly have some really good books still to read! I really enjoyed this one. She writes beautifully descriptive prose and some of her characters are delightful. The two children, Preston and Cordelia, are perfect and I grew quite attached to Dellarobia, Dovey and Hester. I also felt very sorry for Cub who really had never done anything wrong but eventually came out the one who lost the m</span>
  <span id="freeText4289695674154612529" style="display:none">Well that was my first <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/3541.Barbara_Kingsolver" title="Barbara Kingsolver" rel="nofollow noopener">Barbara Kingsolver</a> book and since everyone seems to agree it is not her best then I certainly have some really good books still to read! I really enjoyed this one. She writes beautifully descriptive prose and some of her characters are delightful. The two children, Preston and Cordelia, are perfect and I grew quite attached to Dellarobia, Dovey and Hester. I also felt very sorry for Cub who really had never done anything wrong but eventually came out the one who lost the most. The book has left me with a yearning to visit Mexico one day and see the amazing gathering of the Monarch butterflies myself. Something for my bucket list.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4289695674154612529" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
